SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WORKS OF ART ARE INCLUDED WITH THE UNIVERSITY'S ASSETS, AND ON DISPLAY ON CAMPUS FOR PUBLIC VIEWING.

THE UNIVERSITY AND THE FOUNDATION ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND SECTION 71.26(1)(A) OF THE WISCONSIN STATUTES, RESPECTIVELY. HOWEVER, THE UNIVERSITY IS SUBJECT TO INCOME TAXES ON ANY INCOME THAT IS DERIVED FROM A TRADE OF BUSINESS REGULARLY CARRIED ON AND NOT IN FURTHERANCE OF THE PURPOSES FOR WHICH IT WAS GRANTED EXEMPTION. NO INCOME TAX PROVISION HAS BEEN RECORDED AS NET INCOME, IF ANY, FROM UNRELATED TRADE OR BUSINESS IS INSIGNIFICANT. THE UNIVERSITY FOLLOWS THE ACCOUNTING STANDARDS FOR CONTINGENCIES IN EVALUATING UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THIS GUIDANCE PRESCRIBES RECOGNITION THRESHOLD PRINCIPLES FOR THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION OF TAX POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN ON A TAX RETURN THAT ARE NOT CERTAIN TO BE REALIZED. NO LIABILITY HAS BEEN RECOGNIZED BY THE UNIVERSITY FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AS OF JUNE 30, 2018 OR 2017. THE UNIVERSITY'S TAX RETURNS ARE SUBJECT TO REVIEW AND EXAMINATION BY FEDERAL AND STATE AUTHORITIES.

ALL APPLICATIONS AND ADVERTISING CONTAIN STATEMENTS AS TO THE NONDISCRIMINATORY POLICY OF THE UNIVERSITY.
LAKELAND UNIVERSITY DID NOT RECEIVE ANY FEDERAL OR STATE GRANTS IN FISCAL YEAR 2017-2018.

ALL GRANTS ARE DISBURSED TO THE STUDENTS ACCOUNTS DIRECTLY, ACCORDING TO GOVERNMENT REGULATIONS. ALL OUTSIDE GRANTS ARE APPLIED TO THE STUDENTS ACCOUNTS AS PER THE INSTRUCTIONS FROM THE GRANTOR. LAKELAND UNIVERSITY'S FINANCIAL AID DEPARTMENT MONITORS ALL GRANTS AND SCHOLARSHIPS USING POWERFAIDS SOFTWARE WHICH IS VERIFIED WITH COD BEFORE DISBUSEMENTS ARE PROCESSED. FOR OUTSIDE AND OTHER INSTITUTIONAL AID, THE FINANCIAL AID DEPARTMENT FOLLOWS THE SAME PROCEDURES.

TERMS OF THE PRESIDENT'S EMPLOYMENT REQUIRE THAT HE RESIDES IN ON-CAMPUS HOUSING AT THE EXPENSE OF THE INSTITUTION. THE PRESIDENT RECEIVES USE OF AN INSTITUTIONAL VEHICLE; THE PERCENTAGE OF BUSINESS VERSUS PERSONAL USAGE IS DOCUMENTED. THE PRESIDENT RECEIVES A CLUB MEMBERSHIP, A PORTION OF WHICH IS REPORTABLE INCOME ON FORM W-2. FINALLY, THE PRESIDENT WILL EITHER REIMBURSE THE INSTITUTION OR REPORT INCOME ON FORM W-2 FOR PERSONAL AND COMPANION TRAVEL.
